# Command: rectc x y w h
# Arguments: 
#    'x' (int) x coordinate of the center of the rectangle
#    'y' (int) y coordinate of the center of the rectangle
#    'w' (int) width of the rectangle
#    'h' (int) height of the rectangle
# Description: Creates a rectangle centered on a point
# Note:
# Use example:
bounds 210 210 center invert_y
stroke 0.3;color 200 200 200;grid 200 200 10 10
color 0 0 0; stroke 1
# Example starts
rectc  20 -30 40 30
rectc -50 -50 20 50
rectc -50  50 30 30
rectc  50 -90 80 20
# Creating squares with a for loop
for1 5 10 100 "rectc 50 50 %1$d %1$d"
# There's no real need to align the numbers...
